[
    {
        "content": "<p>When do I need to use it 'intro'? I'm a little confused. Some proofing need 'intro' after 'by', and some dont need.</p>",
        "id": 416763174,
        "sender_full_name": "Hallon",
        "timestamp": 1705665446
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>intro</code> is used when the goal is a forall or implication statement and introduces names for the variables</p>",
        "id": 416763497,
        "sender_full_name": "Mario Carneiro",
        "timestamp": 1705665595
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>But when <code>intro</code> is the very first thing in the proof it is usually preferred to instead put the variables you want to introduce in binders before the <code>:</code> of the theorem statement, which has the same effect</p>",
        "id": 416763654,
        "sender_full_name": "Mario Carneiro",
        "timestamp": 1705665644
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>for example:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kd\">example</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"bp\">∀</span> <span class=\"n\">x</span> <span class=\"n\">y</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">Nat</span><span class=\"o\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">x</span> <span class=\"bp\">+</span> <span class=\"n\">y</span> <span class=\"bp\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">y</span> <span class=\"bp\">+</span> <span class=\"n\">x</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span> <span class=\"kd\">by</span>\n  <span class=\"c1\">-- ⊢ ∀ (x y : Nat), x + y = y + x</span>\n  <span class=\"n\">intro</span> <span class=\"n\">x</span> <span class=\"n\">y</span>\n  <span class=\"c1\">-- x y : Nat</span>\n  <span class=\"c1\">-- ⊢ x + y = y + x</span>\n  <span class=\"n\">apply</span> <span class=\"n\">Nat.add_comm</span>\n\n<span class=\"kd\">example</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">x</span> <span class=\"n\">y</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">Nat</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">x</span> <span class=\"bp\">+</span> <span class=\"n\">y</span> <span class=\"bp\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">y</span> <span class=\"bp\">+</span> <span class=\"n\">x</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span> <span class=\"kd\">by</span>\n  <span class=\"c1\">-- x y : Nat</span>\n  <span class=\"c1\">-- ⊢ x + y = y + x</span>\n  <span class=\"n\">apply</span> <span class=\"n\">Nat.add_comm</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 416764011,
        "sender_full_name": "Mario Carneiro",
        "timestamp": 1705665792
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>OK I think I know, Thanks very much</p>",
